  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This is a pilot observational study to evaluate subjects with chronic kidney disease
      acceptance of an alert device linked to an informational website intended to increase
      recognition of chronic kidney disease, and to guide patients and providers to the safe
      delivery of care required for this disease. Primary device was a bracelet with the
      alternative of a key fob with same information supplied when requested. Patients usage of the
      device was evaluated by survey with Likert scale as to whether the device is 0 = not useful,
      1 = somewhat useful, 2 = extremely useful
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
